<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION A ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="how-to-use">A &nbsp; How to Use This Document</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p>This document is the configuration reference for Meridian Health's Brevo automation system. It is structured in the order you build it in Brevo: first set up the data layer (attributes and tags), then build each automation in sequence.</p>

<p><strong>Who this is for:</strong> The person configuring Brevo. No technical background is assumed beyond familiarity with Brevo's automation builder.</p>

<p><strong>Scope of this document:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Full configuration detail for all 10 stages, including triggers, timing, conditions, and channels</li>
  <li>Verbatim copy for Email 01 (enquiry follow-up) and Email 02 (consultation confirmation), ready to paste into Brevo's template editor</li>
  <li>Stub definitions for stages 03–10 — structure and subject lines are specified; body copy is to be completed by the content team</li>
  <li>All required Brevo contact attributes and segmentation tags</li>
  <li>Operational notes including Genie attachment checklist and template selection logic</li>
</ul>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Tone principle:</strong> Every Meridian communication should feel like a continuation of care, not marketing automation. Clinically authoritative, operationally calm, low cognitive load.
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION B ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="flow-overview">B &nbsp; Flow Overview — All 10 Stages</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p>Three separate Brevo automations cover the full patient journey. They connect via shared contact tags.</p>

<table class="flow">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Stage</th>
      <th>Timing</th>
      <th>Trigger / Condition</th>
      <th>Channel</th>
      <th>Subject / Message</th>
      <th>Objective</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">01</td>
      <td>Immediate</td>
      <td>Enquiry submitted</td>
      <td>Email</td>
      <td><em>Meridian Health — We've received your enquiry</em></td>
      <td>Confirm enquiry receipt</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">02</td>
      <td>+15 mins</td>
      <td>If <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag not applied</td>
      <td>SMS</td>
      <td>Meridian Health follow up</td>
      <td>Increase contact rate</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">03</td>
      <td>+24 hours</td>
      <td>If <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag not applied</td>
      <td>Email</td>
      <td><em>Following your enquiry with Meridian Health</em></td>
      <td>Re-engagement</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">04</td>
      <td>+3 days</td>
      <td>If <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag not applied</td>
      <td>Email</td>
      <td><em>What to expect from an initial consultation</em></td>
      <td>Reduce uncertainty</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">05</td>
      <td>+5 days</td>
      <td>If <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag not applied</td>
      <td>Email</td>
      <td><em>Upper GI, Bariatric &amp; Metabolic care pathways</em></td>
      <td>Education / pathway awareness</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">06</td>
      <td>Immediate</td>
      <td>Tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> applied</td>
      <td>Email</td>
      <td><em>Meridian — Your Initial Consultation</em></td>
      <td>Operational onboarding + forms</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">07</td>
      <td>Immediate</td>
      <td>Tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> applied</td>
      <td>SMS</td>
      <td>Appointment confirmed</td>
      <td>Reduce no-shows</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">08</td>
      <td>72 hrs before <span class="mono">appointment_datetime</span></td>
      <td>Date-based trigger from <span class="mono">appointment_datetime</span></td>
      <td>Email + SMS</td>
      <td><em>Upcoming consultation reminder</em></td>
      <td>Prompt form completion</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">09</td>
      <td>Immediate</td>
      <td>Tag <span class="mono">consult_completed</span> applied</td>
      <td>Email</td>
      <td><em>Your next steps with Meridian</em></td>
      <td>Continuity of care</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="stage-num">10</td>
      <td>Immediate + nurture</td>
      <td><span class="mono">pathway</span> attribute set by surgeon</td>
      <td>Email nurture</td>
      <td>Pathway-specific sequence</td>
      <td>Decision support</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Automation Groupings in Brevo</h3>
<p>Configure these as three separate automation workflows in Brevo:</p>
<table class="attrs">
  <thead><tr><th>Automation Name</th><th>Covers Stages</th><th>Entry Trigger</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><strong>MH — Enquiry Nurture</strong></td><td>01–05</td><td>Enquiry form submitted (API event or Brevo form)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>MH — Booking Confirmation</strong></td><td>06–07</td><td>Tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> applied to contact</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>MH — Pre-Consultation Reminder</strong></td><td>08</td><td>Date: 72 hrs before <span class="mono">appointment_datetime</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>MH — Post-Consultation</strong></td><td>09</td><td>Tag <span class="mono">consult_completed</span> applied to contact</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>MH — Pathway: [Name]</strong></td><td>10 (×5)</td><td>Contact attribute <span class="mono">pathway</span> = specific value</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION C ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="brevo-setup">C &nbsp; Brevo Setup: Contact Attributes &amp; Tags</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p>Before building any automations, create the following in Brevo under <strong>Contacts → Settings → Contact Attributes</strong> and configure tags as listed below. These are referenced throughout every automation.</p>

<h2>Contact Attributes</h2>

<table class="attrs">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Attribute Name</th>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>Description</th>
      <th>Set By</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">enquiry_submitted_date</td>
      <td>Date</td>
      <td>Date and time enquiry form was submitted</td>
      <td>Enquiry form / API on submission</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">appointment_datetime</td>
      <td>Date / DateTime</td>
      <td>Scheduled consultation date and time. Used by Stage 08 date-based trigger.</td>
      <td>Genie PMS sync / manual Brevo update on booking</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">consultation_booked</td>
      <td>Boolean</td>
      <td>True once an appointment is confirmed in Genie. Mirrors the <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag.</td>
      <td>Genie sync / admin</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">consultation_completed</td>
      <td>Boolean</td>
      <td>True once consultation has taken place. Mirrors the <span class="mono">consult_completed</span> tag.</td>
      <td>Genie sync / admin post-consultation</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">pathway</td>
      <td>Text (enumerated)</td>
      <td>Surgeon-recommended care pathway. Valid values: <span class="mono">sleeve</span>, <span class="mono">bypass</span>, <span class="mono">reflux_uppergi</span>, <span class="mono">glp1_metabolic</span>, <span class="mono">revision</span></td>
      <td>Clinician / admin post-consultation</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">clinician</td>
      <td>Text</td>
      <td>Assigned clinician code. Values: <span class="mono">SW</span> (Dr Sherson), <span class="mono">NW</span> (Dr [NW]), <span class="mono">MH</span> (A/Prof Michael Hii)</td>
      <td>Admin on booking</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">appointment_type</td>
      <td>Text</td>
      <td>Appointment modality. Values: <span class="mono">face_to_face</span> or <span class="mono">telehealth</span></td>
      <td>Admin on booking</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Segmentation Tags</h2>
<p>In Brevo, tags are applied to contacts and can be used as automation triggers and conditions. Create the following tags in <strong>Contacts → Tags</strong>.</p>

<table class="attrs">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Tag</th>
      <th>Purpose</th>
      <th>Applied When</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">enquiry_uppergi</span></td>
      <td>Identifies Upper GI leads</td>
      <td>Enquiry form indicates Upper GI / reflux concern</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">enquiry_bariatric</span></td>
      <td>Identifies Bariatric leads</td>
      <td>Enquiry form indicates bariatric interest</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">enquiry_metabolic</span></td>
      <td>Identifies GLP-1 / metabolic leads</td>
      <td>Enquiry form indicates metabolic / GLP-1 interest</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">booked_consult</span></td>
      <td>Consultation has been booked</td>
      <td>Appointment created in Genie. <strong>This tag exits the contact from the Enquiry Nurture sequence (stages 01–05) and triggers the Booking Confirmation automation (stages 06–07).</strong></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">consult_completed</span></td>
      <td>Consultation has occurred</td>
      <td>Post-consultation, admin marks appointment complete</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">telehealth</span></td>
      <td>Appointment is via Coviu</td>
      <td>Booking confirmed as telehealth. Controls conditional block in Email 02.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">face_to_face</span></td>
      <td>Appointment is in-clinic</td>
      <td>Booking confirmed as face-to-face. Controls conditional block in Email 02.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">forms_completed</span></td>
      <td>Patient has submitted all pre-consultation forms</td>
      <td>Forms returned to clinic</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span class="tag">referral_received</span></td>
      <td>GP referral received by clinic</td>
      <td>Referral document received and filed</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Critical:</strong> The <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag is the primary handoff signal across automations. When it is applied to a contact, two things must happen simultaneously in Brevo: (1) the Enquiry Nurture automation exits the contact, and (2) the Booking Confirmation automation begins. Configure the exit condition on the Enquiry Nurture automation as: <em>"Contact has tag booked_consult"</em> — check this at every wait/condition node.
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 1 ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="enquiry-nurture">1 &nbsp; Enquiry Nurture Automation — Stages 01–05</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p><strong>Automation name in Brevo:</strong> MH — Enquiry Nurture</p>
<p><strong>Entry trigger:</strong> Contact submits enquiry form (Brevo form submission event, or API call <span class="mono">track</span> event named <span class="mono">enquiry_submitted</span>)</p>
<p><strong>Global exit condition:</strong> At every wait and condition node, add an exit rule: <em>contact has tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span></em>. The contact exits immediately when this tag is applied — do not wait for the next scheduled step.</p>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>How to configure the exit in Brevo:</strong> In the automation builder, after each Wait step, add a Condition branch. One branch checks whether <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag is absent (continue nurture); the other branch leads to an Exit node. Alternatively, use Brevo's automation "Exit conditions" global setting if available on your plan.
</div>

<!-- STAGE 01 -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <p class="stage-label">Stage 01 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Enquiry Nurture</p>
  <p class="stage-title">Enquiry Follow-Up Email</p>
  <div class="stage-meta">
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Timing</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Immediate — send as soon as contact enters the automation</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Channel</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Email</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Template name</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">MH — Email 01 — Enquiry Follow-Up</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">From name</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Meridian Health</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Condition</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">None — send immediately to all entrants</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Email 01 Template — Verbatim Copy</h3>
<p class="note">Paste the following into Brevo's template editor. Use the merge tag <span class="mono">{{ contact.FIRSTNAME }}</span> for [First Name].</p>

<div class="email-block">
  <p class="email-subject">Subject line</p>
  <p class="email-subject-line">Meridian Health — We've received your enquiry</p>
  <div class="email-body">
    <p>Hi {{ contact.FIRSTNAME }},</p>
    <p>Following your recent enquiry, our team attempted to contact you regarding an initial consultation with one of our clinicians.</p>
    <p>To arrange a consultation, please contact the clinic on <strong>(03) 9416 4418</strong> or reply to this email.</p>
    <p>Meridian Health provides Upper Gastrointestinal, Bariatric and Metabolic care including assessment, treatment planning, structured follow-up and ongoing clinical support.</p>
    <p>If you have any questions prior to booking, our team would be happy to assist.</p>
    <p>Kind regards,<br/>
    Meridian Health<br/>
    Brenan Place, Fitzroy</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- STAGE 02 -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <p class="stage-label">Stage 02 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Enquiry Nurture</p>
  <p class="stage-title">Follow-Up SMS</p>
  <div class="stage-meta">
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Timing</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">+15 minutes after Stage 01 email is sent</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Channel</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">SMS — wired to contact's mobile field (<span class="mono">contact.SMS</span> or <span class="mono">contact.MOBILE</span>)</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Condition</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Contact does NOT have tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Exit if</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Contact has tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> → exit automation</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>SMS 02 — Message Copy</h3>
<div class="email-block">
  <p class="email-body">
    Hi {{ contact.FIRSTNAME }}, thank you for contacting Meridian Health. A member of our team will be in touch shortly regarding your enquiry. You can also reach us on (03) 9416 4418.
  </p>
  <p class="note" style="margin-top:8pt;">Keep under 160 characters if possible. The above is approximately 175 characters — split across two SMS if cost is a concern, or abbreviate to: <em>"Hi [First Name], thanks for contacting Meridian Health. Our team will be in touch shortly — or call us on (03) 9416 4418."</em></p>
</div>

<!-- STAGE 03 -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <p class="stage-label">Stage 03 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Enquiry Nurture</p>
  <p class="stage-title">Re-Engagement Email — Stub</p>
  <div class="stage-meta">
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Timing</span>
