      <span class="stage-meta-key">Template name</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">MH — Email 04 — Consultation Overview (3 day) [STUB]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Condition</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Contact does NOT have tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Exit if</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Contact has tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> → exit automation</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Objective</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Reduce uncertainty. Demystify the consultation process. Help patient understand what to expect before they commit to booking.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="note" style="margin-top:8pt;"><strong>Content team brief:</strong> Walk through a typical initial consultation: assessment, discussion, no obligation, opportunity to ask questions. Tone: reassuring and practical. No clinical jargon. Reference that consultations are available face-to-face or via telehealth (Coviu). Approximately 120–160 words.</p>
</div>

