      <span class="stage-meta-key">Objective</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Education on the breadth of Meridian's three care areas. Position Meridian as comprehensive, not single-service. Soft CTA to book.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="note" style="margin-top:8pt;"><strong>Content team brief:</strong> Brief overview of Upper GI (reflux, oesophageal, hiatus hernia), Bariatric (sleeve, bypass, revision) and Metabolic Medicine (GLP-1, weight management, long-term metabolic care). Reinforce the key positioning line: <em>"Different pathways exist because different patients exist."</em> Closing CTA to contact or book. Approximately 140–180 words.</p>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 2 ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="booking-confirmation">2 &nbsp; Booking Confirmation Automation — Stages 06–07</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p><strong>Automation name in Brevo:</strong> MH — Booking Confirmation</p>
<p><strong>Entry trigger:</strong> Tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> is applied to contact</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> This automation begins the moment <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> is applied — the same event that exits the contact from the Enquiry Nurture (stages 01–05). Both happen simultaneously.</p>
<p>Before sending Stage 06, ensure the following contact attributes are populated: <span class="mono">appointment_datetime</span>, <span class="mono">clinician</span>, <span class="mono">appointment_type</span> (face_to_face or telehealth), and that either <span class="tag">telehealth</span> or <span class="tag">face_to_face</span> tag has been applied.</p>

<!-- STAGE 06 -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <p class="stage-label">Stage 06 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Booking Confirmation</p>
  <p class="stage-title">Consultation Confirmation Email</p>
  <div class="stage-meta">
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Timing</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Immediate — on entry (tag <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> applied)</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Channel</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Email</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Template name</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">MH — Email 02 — Consultation Confirmation</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Conditional blocks</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Block A: face-to-face (tag <span class="mono">face_to_face</span>) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Block B: telehealth (tag <span class="mono">telehealth</span>) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Block C: clinician variant (<span class="mono">clinician</span> attribute = SW / NW / MH)</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Attachments</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Confirmation consultation letter &nbsp;·&nbsp; Heidi information and consent documentation</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Email 02 Template — Verbatim Copy</h3>
<p class="note">The email body below contains three conditional blocks, marked in dashed boxes. In Brevo's drag-and-drop or HTML editor, use <strong>conditional content visibility rules</strong> on each block to show/hide based on the relevant tag or attribute value.</p>

<div class="email-block">
  <p class="email-subject">Subject line</p>
  <p class="email-subject-line">Meridian — Your Initial Consultation</p>
  <div class="email-body">
    <p>Hi {{ contact.FIRSTNAME }},</p>
    <p>Please find the required forms below to complete prior to your upcoming consultation with {{ contact.CLINICIAN }} on {{ contact.APPOINTMENT_DATE }} at {{ contact.APPOINTMENT_TIME }}.</p>
    <p>Please also refer to the attached confirmation letter for important information relating to your appointment.</p>
    <p><strong>Required prior to consultation:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Patient Registration Form</li>
      <li>Relevant clinical questionnaire</li>
      <li>GP referral (if your GP has not already forwarded this to us)</li>
      <li>Relevant pathology or imaging from the past 12 months</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="conditional-block">
    <p class="conditional-label">Conditional Block A — Face-to-Face appointments only<br/>
    <span style="font-weight:normal;">Show this block when: contact has tag <span class="mono">face_to_face</span></span></p>
    <div class="email-body">
      <p>Our clinic is located at:</p>
      <p>
        Brenan Place<br/>
        Level [X]<br/>
        Victoria Parade<br/>
        Fitzroy VIC 3065
      </p>
      <p>Paid parking is available on surrounding streets and within nearby car parks.</p>
      <p>Public transport access is available via Victoria Parade and surrounding tram routes.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="conditional-block">
    <p class="conditional-label">Conditional Block B — Telehealth (Coviu) appointments only<br/>
    <span style="font-weight:normal;">Show this block when: contact has tag <span class="mono">telehealth</span></span></p>
    <div class="email-body">
      <p>Your consultation will be conducted via Coviu (telehealth).</p>
      <p>At the time of your appointment, please use the link below to enter the virtual waiting room as a guest:</p>
      <p><strong>[Join Coviu]</strong></p>
      <p>For the best experience:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Desktop, laptop and Android users: Google Chrome or Firefox recommended</li>
        <li>iPhone or iPad users: Safari recommended</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Please ensure you are in a quiet and private location where you are comfortable discussing your health information.</p>
      <p>You are welcome to have a support person present during your consultation if preferred.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="email-body" style="margin-top:10pt;">
    <p>This practice also uses Heidi, a secure clinical documentation support tool used to assist with note-taking during consultations. Please refer to the attached information sheet and consent details included within the registration forms.</p>
    <p><strong>Attached to this email:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Confirmation consultation letter</li>
      <li>Heidi information and consent documentation</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If you have any questions prior to your appointment, please contact the clinic or reply to this email and our team will be happy to assist.</p>
    <p>Kind regards,<br/>
    Meridian Health<br/>
    Upper GI, Bariatric &amp; Metabolic Care</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Clinician Variant (Conditional Block C)</h3>
<p>Add a conditional content section above or below the clinician name merge tag for any clinician-specific content (e.g. specific preparation instructions, different forms). Initially this can simply control the display of the clinician's full name and title:</p>

<table class="attrs">
  <thead><tr><th>Condition</th><th>Clinician Display Name</th><th>Merge Tag Value</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><span class="mono">clinician</span> = <span class="mono">SW</span></td><td>Dr [Surname], Surgeon</td><td>Set <span class="mono">contact.CLINICIAN</span> on booking</td></tr>
    <tr><td><span class="mono">clinician</span> = <span class="mono">NW</span></td><td>Dr [Surname], Surgeon</td><td>Set <span class="mono">contact.CLINICIAN</span> on booking</td></tr>
    <tr><td><span class="mono">clinician</span> = <span class="mono">MH</span></td><td>A/Prof Michael Hii, Oesophago-Gastric &amp; Bariatric Surgeon</td><td>Set <span class="mono">contact.CLINICIAN</span> on booking</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p class="note">Populate <span class="mono">contact.CLINICIAN</span>, <span class="mono">contact.APPOINTMENT_DATE</span>, and <span class="mono">contact.APPOINTMENT_TIME</span> as contact attributes at the time of booking in Genie. These must be pushed to Brevo before Stage 06 sends.</p>

