    </div>
    <div class="stage-meta-row">
      <span class="stage-meta-key">Objective</span>
      <span class="stage-meta-val">Continuity of care. Acknowledge the consultation has occurred. Provide a clear, calm outline of what happens next based on the patient's pathway.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Email 09 — Content Brief (Stub)</h3>
<div class="email-block">
  <p class="note"><strong>Content team brief:</strong> Thank the patient for attending. Briefly acknowledge that next steps will be communicated by the clinical team. Reinforce that they are well-supported. If <span class="mono">pathway</span> attribute is already set, this email can optionally reference the pathway name. Tone: warm, calm, clinical authority. Approximately 80–120 words. This email bridges to Stage 10 pathway-specific nurture — do not replicate content from Stage 10 here.</p>
</div>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Handoff to Stage 10:</strong> After Stage 09 sends, the surgeon or admin sets the <span class="mono">pathway</span> attribute on the contact. This triggers the relevant Stage 10 pathway automation. The two events may be close in time but operate independently.
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 5 ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="pathway-nurture">5 &nbsp; Pathway-Specific Nurture Tracks — Stage 10</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p><strong>Entry trigger (all five tracks):</strong> Contact attribute <span class="mono">pathway</span> is set to the corresponding value by surgeon or admin recommendation post-consultation.</p>
<p><strong>Structure:</strong> Create five separate automations in Brevo, one per pathway. Each begins immediately when the relevant <span class="mono">pathway</span> value is set. All are stubs — structure and subject lines are defined; body copy is to be completed by the content team.</p>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Pathway to category mapping:</strong><br/>
  <strong>Upper GI:</strong> reflux, hiatus hernia, oesophageal conditions, gastric concerns, revision surgery<br/>
  <strong>Bariatric:</strong> sleeve gastrectomy, gastric bypass, revision procedures, surgical suitability<br/>
  <strong>Metabolic Medicine:</strong> GLP-1 / clinician-guided weight management, nutrition, long-term metabolic care
</div>

