<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION D ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="operational-notes">D &nbsp; Operational Notes &amp; Genie Attachment Checklist</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p>The following notes should be added as the description or internal notes on each relevant Brevo automation. They are reproduced here for reference and for handoff to admin staff.</p>

<h2>Genie Attachment Checklist</h2>
<p>The following documents must be attached in Genie and transferred to Brevo's Email 02 template for every consultation booking. These are sent as email attachments in Stage 06.</p>

<table class="attrs">
  <thead><tr><th>Document</th><th>Always Required?</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Confirmation consultation letter</td>
      <td>Yes — all appointment types</td>
      <td>Generated from Genie on booking. Attach to Email 02 before (or at) send time. Contains appointment specifics, cancellation policy, and clinician details.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Heidi information sheet and consent documentation</td>
      <td>Yes — all appointment types</td>
      <td>Heidi is the AI clinical documentation tool used during consultations. Patients must receive and consent via this documentation. Included in registration form packet.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Patient Registration Form</td>
      <td>Yes — all new patients</td>
      <td>Clinic's standard registration document. Return to clinic before consultation. Included in email body as a required pre-consultation item.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Relevant clinical questionnaire</td>
      <td>Yes — pathway-appropriate version</td>
      <td>Select the appropriate questionnaire based on enquiry type: Upper GI, Bariatric, or Metabolic. Attach correct version in Genie before triggering Brevo send.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Template Selection Logic</h2>
<p>When preparing Email 02 (Stage 06) for sending, the following checks must be completed before the <span class="mono">booked_consult</span> tag is applied in Brevo (which triggers the send):</p>

<table class="attrs">
  <thead><tr><th>Check</th><th>Brevo Tag / Attribute to Set</th><th>Controls</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Is the appointment face-to-face or telehealth?</td>
      <td>Apply tag <span class="tag">face_to_face</span> OR <span class="tag">telehealth</span></td>
      <td>Conditional Block A (clinic address) or Block B (Coviu instructions)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Which clinician?</td>
      <td>Set attribute <span class="mono">clinician</span> = SW / NW / MH</td>
      <td>Clinician display name in email body; future clinician-specific content blocks</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Is <span class="mono">appointment_datetime</span> set?</td>
      <td>Set attribute <span class="mono">appointment_datetime</span></td>
      <td>Stage 08 date-based reminder trigger; merge tags in Email 02 and SMS 07</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Is <span class="mono">appointment_date</span> and <span class="mono">appointment_time</span> set for display?</td>
      <td>Set attributes <span class="mono">APPOINTMENT_DATE</span> and <span class="mono">APPOINTMENT_TIME</span></td>
      <td>Human-readable date/time in email and SMS bodies</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Are Genie attachments ready?</td>
      <td>Attach in Genie; upload to Brevo template if using static files</td>
      <td>Attachments on Email 02</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Brevo Automation Descriptions (copy into Brevo)</h2>
<p class="note">Paste the text below into the Description field of each Brevo automation for operational clarity.</p>

<h4>MH — Enquiry Nurture</h4>
<p style="font-family: Courier New, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt; border: 1pt solid #ddd; padding: 8pt; background: #fafafa;">
Triggers on enquiry submission. Sends Email 01 immediately, then nurtures over 5 days with exit condition on booked_consult tag. Stage 02 is SMS (+15 min). Stages 03–05 are email stubs (24hr / 3 day / 5 day). Every step checks: if booked_consult tag applied, exit automation. Do not modify wait times without updating this document.
</p>

<h4>MH — Booking Confirmation</h4>
<p style="font-family: Courier New, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt; border: 1pt solid #ddd; padding: 8pt; background: #fafafa;">
Triggers when booked_consult tag applied. Before triggering: ensure appointment_datetime, clinician, face_to_face or telehealth tag, and APPOINTMENT_DATE / APPOINTMENT_TIME attributes are set. Sends Email 02 (consultation confirmation with conditional blocks) and SMS 07 simultaneously. Genie attachments: confirmation letter, Heidi info sheet, registration forms, relevant questionnaire.
</p>

<h4>MH — Pre-Consultation Reminder</h4>
<p style="font-family: Courier New, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt; border: 1pt solid #ddd; padding: 8pt; background: #fafafa;">
Date-based automation. Fires 72 hours before appointment_datetime. Sends reminder email (stub) and SMS to prompt form completion. Requires appointment_datetime attribute to be populated at booking. Conditional blocks: face_to_face / telehealth — same as Email 02.
</p>

<h4>MH — Post-Consultation</h4>
<p style="font-family: Courier New, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt; border: 1pt solid #ddd; padding: 8pt; background: #fafafa;">
Triggers when consult_completed tag applied by admin. Sends Email 09 (next steps stub) immediately. After sending, surgeon or admin sets the pathway attribute — this triggers the relevant Stage 10 pathway automation independently.
</p>

<h4>MH — Pathway automations (all five)</h4>
<p style="font-family: Courier New, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt; border: 1pt solid #ddd; padding: 8pt; background: #fafafa;">
Triggers when pathway attribute is set to the corresponding value (sleeve / bypass / reflux_uppergi / glp1_metabolic / revision). Each track contains 3 email stubs at immediate / +3-4 days / +7-10 days. Body copy to be completed by content team. Do not activate until copy is populated and reviewed clinically.
</p>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ SECTION E ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h1 id="future-sequences">E &nbsp; Future Email Sequences — Content Team Handoff</h1>
<hr class="section-rule"/>

<p>The following sequences are planned but <strong>out of scope for this build</strong>. They are documented here for handoff to the content team and for future Brevo automation development. Do not build these as active automations until copy is complete and reviewed.</p>

<table class="attrs">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Sequence</th>
      <th>Purpose</th>
      <th>Audience</th>
      <th>Priority</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><em>What happens during an initial consultation</em></td>
      <td>Reduce pre-booking anxiety. Demystify the consultation process.</td>
      <td>All enquiry contacts (could enrich Stage 04 stub)</td>
      <td>High</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><em>Are GLP-1s the answer or part of the solution?</em></td>
      <td>Educational positioning — metabolic medicine public acquisition flow</td>
      <td>Metabolic / GLP-1 leads</td>
      <td>High</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><em>Understanding reflux and Upper GI symptoms</em></td>
      <td>Upper GI nurture — specialist credibility</td>
      <td>Upper GI leads</td>
      <td>Medium</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><em>Life after bariatric surgery</em></td>
      <td>Post-op nurture / continuity of care</td>
      <td>Post-surgical bariatric patients</td>
      <td>Medium</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><em>Understanding metabolic medicine</em></td>
      <td>GLP-1 patient education nurture</td>
      <td>GLP-1 / metabolic pathway patients</td>
      <td>Medium</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><em>Preparing for surgery</em></td>
      <td>Pre-op sequence — practical and psychological preparation</td>
      <td>Surgical pathway patients pre-op</td>
      <td>Medium</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><em>Your first weeks after surgery</em></td>
      <td>Post-op sequence — recovery, nutrition, follow-up</td>
      <td>Post-surgical patients</td>
      <td>Medium</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>GP Referrer Flow</td>
      <td>Strengthen referral relationships. Introduce Meridian to referring GPs.</td>
      <td>GP contacts / referrers</td>
      <td>Future</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Dormant Lead Re-Engagement</td>
      <td>Soft reactivation of contacts with no booking and no engagement after 60+ days</td>
      <td>Inactive leads</td>
      <td>Future</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Communication principle — for all future content:</strong> Every Meridian communication should feel like a continuation of care, not marketing automation. The patient should feel guided, informed and supported at every stage. Tone: calm, intelligent, medically authoritative, emotionally safe.
</div>

